raw_mentions: Figure 3 shows the results of a plaque inhibition assay using Vero cells of the SARS-CoV-2 plaque inhibition assay, in which IFN α 2a (a commercially available subtype) was compared to IFN α 14 and shows an IC 50-indicating that α -14 is 20X more potent against Covid19 virus than α -2 a.
